1933;;The Mad Game;;American;;Irving Cummings;;Spencer Tracy, Claire Trevor, J. Carrol Naish;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Mad_Game;;The film concerns an imprisoned bootlegger (Spencer Tracy) recruited from incarceration to help capture his own gang after they kidnap the daughter (Claire Trevor) of the judge who jailed him. The supporting cast includes Ralph Morgan, J. Carrol Naish, Matt McHugh, and Paul Fix, and the movie was directed by Irving Cummings.